these nukes could have resistances checks against poison,disease,cold, we already have the other two. and they could be evoc type spells maybe. This way it might give mages a choice to specialize or respecialize but thats a differant subject. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uomel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Omel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#333333>(9/12/02 5:27:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> PoP New Spell Ideas</span><hr size=1> I have a number of ideas. I would like my peers in the magician community to think of encounters like the Vinicator, Doomshade, Rumblecrush, Thought Horror Overfiend, The Shissra Emporer. Now compare those encounters to Phinigel Autropos, Venril Sathir, and the Dracoliche The game has gotten much more challenging my friends and I firmly believe the magician class has not been improved upon to meet those new challenges in the ways that other classes have. We are still balanced for battles of old Norrath and with Planes of power on the horizon it is painfully clear we are no longer the power we once were. <br>
<br>
1. The epic pet should rise in level with the magician using it. The pet should start at 49 and then for each level the magician has from 56 up the pet should go up one level gaining an appropriate boost in resists, attack and other statistics. Giving the raiding end game magician something to look forward to rather than a good laugh about how the druid DoT that landed did more damage than the epic pet managed the entire fight. And enable magicians to compete with power of dire charm.<br>
<br>
Ex. Epic pet 49th level summoned by a 55th level magician<br>
Hp 4000<br>
Max melee hit 81<br>
Proc 143<br>
Stun 80<br>
<br>
Ex. Epic pet 54th level summoned by a 60th level magician<br>
Hp 5500 (an increase of 300 hp per level 56+)<br>
Max melee hit 111 (an increase of 6 points of damage per level 56+)<br>
Proc 293 (an increase if 30 points of damage per level 56+)<br>
Stun 105 (an increase of 5 points of damage per level 56+)<br>
<br>
Further the Epic pet is indeed deserving of its own model HOWEVER after the dissatisfaction I feel over the new Erudites, new skeletons, and new elementals I for one would like to see and be able to vote upon concept art before a new change to the pets look is made.<br>
<br>
2. Rather than Bane Pets, I suggest bane burn outs. Something for the uber magicians to look forward to rather than an ancient spell that increase our damage by a whopping 120 pts. These Bane Burn Outs should be acquired by quest and/or boss monster defeat. I must admit this idea would only be balanced if it is possible for programming to tell the difference between a froglok and Trakanon at an instants notice should the pet change targets between the two. Still we are the pet class and this idea serves to empower pets and therefor the magicians that use them.<br>
<br>
An Example<br>
Rage of the Sleeper<br>
Level: 60<br>
Mana: 150<br>
School: Alteration<br>
Type: Pet only buff effective against dragons only<br>
Max Duration: 15 minutes<br>
Casting Time: 6 Seconds<br>
Recast time: 180 Seconds<br>
Actual Effects: Pet Increase AC 35 (only if attacked by dragon class monster)<br>
Pet Increase Strength 80 (only if attacking a dragon class monster)<br>
Pet Increase Attack Speed 80 (only against dragon class monsters) <br>
Pet Gains Immunity to Effect Dragon Roar Spell<br>
Pet Gains resist boosts +25 to effects of Fire, Cold, and Poison<br>
<br>
I suggest there be Giant, Shissar, Summoned, peg legged pony and Gnome Bane Burn Outs with similar effects  <br>
<br>
3. AE pets. Not for the dreaded AE grouping the powers that be dislike so much. I can think of numerous occasions where such a pet would be beneficial that are already in the game. Like the skeleton battle for the Katta Shield Quest, the 8th Coldain Shawl battle or the 10th Coldain Ring War battle. These are very entertaining encounters and I hope Planes of Power will bring us more like them. The idea is there with Dyzils Deafening Decoy but lets face it the pet is not practical or effective. If it were it would be used more often rather than a subject of debate.<br>
<br>
These pets should other wise be equal to the 57 through 60 elementals with these exceptions.<br>
<br>
<br>
Level 57 Sylph (female genie model, in white color scheme) similar to the much needed to be improved upon Gr. Voc Air pet <br>
Pet Proc point blank AoE magic stun for 80<br>
<br>
Level 58 Undine (male genie model, in blue color scheme)<br>
Water pet similar to Gr. Voc Water (I suggest it loose the backstab ability however)<br>
Pet proc point blank AoE cold for 125 points of damage to all npc targets <br>
<br>
Level 59 Dao (male genie model in black and brown)<br>
Earth Pet similar to Gr. Voc Earth <br>
Pet Proc point blank AoE magic root for 80 points of damage<br>
<br>
Level 60 Ifrit (female genie model in red color scheme)<br>
Bearing no similiarities to the 58 fire pet as this pet would need to be tougher and would have only one<br>
spell. <br>
Pet Proc point blank AoE fire for 125 points of damage to all npc targets<br>
<br>
4. Frenzied Burn Out. Its been said but I dont see that as an excuse not to say it again. Frenzied Burn Out. Was that some kind of joke? Fix it please. It needs a better effect for the pet, much, much longer duration and unresistable, tremendously higher damage explotion at the end. Yes I said UNRESISTABLE. This is our version of manaburn folks we deserve nothing less.<br>
<br>
5. New Pet buffs. I have some ideas for some pet buffs in the spirit of beastlords to increase the power and utility of our pets.<br>
<br>
Level: 51 Dirt of Brell <br>
Mana: 100<br>
School: Alteration<br>
Type: Earth or Epic Pet only buff<br>
Max Duration: 15 minutes<br>
Casting Time: 6 Seconds<br>
Recast time: 12 Seconds<br>
Actual Effects: earth or epic pet gains additional magic based snare and damage over time proc. Reduce Targets movement speed by 55% deals 360 points of damage over 60 seconds.<br>
<br>
Level 52 Fires of Ro<br>
Mana: 100<br>
School: Alteration<br>
Type: Fire or Epic Pet buff<br>
Max Duration: 15minutes<br>
Casting Time: 6 Seconds<br>
Recast Time: 12 Seconds<br>
Actual Effects: Fire or epic pet gains an additional fire based damage over time proc that deals 360 points of damage over time and reduces targets fire resist by 25 for 60 seconds.<br>
<br>
<br>
Level 53 Winds of Karana<br>
Mana:100<br>
School: Alteration<br>
Type: Air or Epic Pet buff<br>
Max Duration: 15minutes<br>
Casting time: 6 seconds<br>
Recast time: 12 seconds<br>
Actual Effects: Air or Epic pet gains gains an additional magic based air proc that deals 360 points of damage over time and reduces targets strength by 25 and attack by 50 for 60 seconds.<br>
<br>
Level 54 Waters of Quellios<br>
Mana:100<br>
School: Alteration<br>
Type: Water or Epic Pet buff<br>
Max Duration: 15minutes<br>
Casting Time: 6 seconds<br>
Recast Time: 12 Seconds<br>
Actual Effects: Water or Epic pet gains and additional cold based proc that deals 360 points of damage over time and reduces targets attacking speed by 50% for 60 seconds.<br>
<br>
Naturally these spells once again will make it possbile for pets to break Enchenter Mesmerizations meaning greater skill and caution employed by the magician.<br>
<br>
Level 55 Elemental Water<br>
Mana:150<br>
School: Alteration<br>
Type: Epic or Water pet buff<br>
Max Duration: 10 minutes<br>
Casting Time: 9 Seconds<br>
Recast time: 18 seconds<br>
Actual Effects: Water or Epic pet gains a low resist cold proc that does 100 points of damage <br>
<br>
Level 56 Elemental Air<br>
Mana: 150<br>
School: Alteration<br>
Type: Epic or Air pet buff<br>
Max Duration: 10 minues<br>
Casting Time: 9 seconds<br>
Recast Time: 18 Seconds<br>
Actual Effects: Air or Epic pet gains a low resist magic proc that does 100 points of damage<br>
<br>
Level 57 Elemental Fire<br>
Mana: 150<br>
School: Alteration<br>
Type: Epic or Fire pet buff<br>
Casting Time: 9 seconds<br>
Recast Time: 18 Seconds<br>
Actual Effects: Fire or Epic pet gains a low resist fire proc that does 100 points of damage<br>
<br>
Level 58 Elemental Earth<br>
Mana: 150<br>
School: Alteration<br>
Tyoe: Epic or Earth pet buff<br>
Casting Time: 9 Seconds<br>
Recast Time: 18 Seconds<br>
Actual Effects: Earth or Epic pet gains a low resist disease proc that does 100 points of damage<br>
<br>
5. Changes to Existing Spells<br>
Seeking Flame of Sekuer should have its level reduced to 55<br>
Shock of Fiery Blades should have its damage increased to 1200 (lets not forget this spell was their anemic apology for yanking Summoning Shield from the spell list at the very last second before Shdows of Luclin was released)<br>
Ancient: Shock of the Sun should have its damage increased to 1615<br>
<br>
6. New Spell ideas <br>
A bolt spell at 59 dealing 1515 points of damage to replace the lowered in level seeking flame<br>
A New Magic mased Shock at 60 dealing 1125<br>
A COLD based AE line rather than DD since they want to be stingy culminating with a 60th level 3 wave rain AE that deals 675 per wave<br>
Summoned: Boots with Effect Shadow Step<br>
Summoned: Cloak with Effect Invisibility<br>
Summoned: Mask of Mysteries Spell that temporarily changes the character to a random race / gender / and model of the zone.  Much like the Illusion Effects of the creatures in Grieg's End.  This is a &quot;Just for Fun&quot; spell that I think would be awesome.<br>
